{"type":"message","id":"c54aa1ba","parentId":"4cc22547","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:41:28.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The workspace folder doesn't exist. Let me just recreate the hourly email check cron properly - one that only tells me about NEW emails I haven't already told Bobby about.\n\nThe key insight from the conversation: Bobby doesn't want to hear about the same email multiple times. So I need to track which emails I've already reported. Let me set up a simple tracking mechanism and recreate the cron.\n\nLet me write a smarter script and recreate the cron.\n","thinkingSignature":"5a7442be72d440a396aef975ad63c86ac21920b2facc30c460beaf6c213884f8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nMy bad — I misread the request. You wanted me to stop repeating myself, not kill the whole check. Let me turn it back on with smarter logic so it only reports NEW emails, not the same ones over and over.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ikwquja7rvuo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /tmp/emmy_email_check.sh << 'EOF'\n#!/bin/bash\n# Emmy's smart hourly email check - only reports NEW unseen emails\n\nTRACK_FILE=\"/tmp/emmy_last_email_id\"\n\n# Get latest unread email\nLATEST=$(gog email list --unread --limit 1 2>/dev/null | head -5)\n\nif [ -z \"$LATEST\" ]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n# Extract message ID or subject as identifier\nEMAIL_ID=$(echo \"$LATEST\" | grep -i \"subject\" | cut -d: -f2- | tr -d ' ' | head -c 50)\n\n# Check if we've already reported this\nLAST_REPORTED=$(cat \"$TRACK_FILE\" 2>/dev/null)\n\nif [ \"$EMAIL_ID\" != \"$LAST_REPORTED\" ]; then\n  # New email - report it and update tracking\n  echo \"$LATEST\"\n  echo \"$EMAIL_ID\" > \"$TRACK_FILE\"\n  echo \"NEW_EMAIL\"\nelse\n  # Already reported - stay silent\n  exit 0\nfi\nEOF\nchmod +x /tmp/emmy_email_check.sh\necho \"Script created\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99,"output":404,"cache