{"type":"message","id":"2f942257","parentId":"abb847e5","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:43:10.138Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is the script outputs the full result and I need to parse it better. Let me fix the extraction. But actually, the core problem is that I misunderstood Bobby's request. He wants me to:\n\n1. Keep the hourly email check cron job\n2. But only tell him about emails I haven't told him about before (deduplication)\n\nI killed the cron entirely when I should have kept it and fixed the deduplication logic. Let me restore the cron job with the smart deduplication built in.\n","thinkingSignature":"a4ce5062db8b5d72f6e1ff99911a1bf3af1139c9e2e1beec9279a8a21403a23a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it — I misunderstood. You wanted to keep the hourly check, just stop repeating the same emails. Let me restore it with smart deduplication:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sky94h577z7w_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"Emmy Smart Email Check","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Emmy. Run /tmp/emmy_email_check_agent.sh and check /tmp/emmy_last_email_id. If it outputs 'NEW_EMAIL_FOUND', look up the latest unread email with: gog email search \"is:unread\" --limit 1 --plain\n\nIf there is a new email, send a brief Telegram message to 8212808444 with the subject and sender only. If no new email or already reported, say nothing.","timeoutSeconds":30},"schedule":{"everyMs":3600000,"kind":"every"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","delivery":{"channel":"telegram","mode":"announce","to":"8212808444"}}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104,"output":343,"cacheRead":30400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777686180205,"responseId":"064489a48acbf17c85ceb58f0e6e76a6"}}
