{"type":"message","id":"e0a790b7","parentId":"1988c830","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:43:30.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it's still outputting \"NEW_EMAIL_FOUND\" when running again. Let me check why.\n\nActually, looking at the script again - the issue is that the `if` condition checks `if [ \"$EMAIL_ID\" = \"$LAST\" ]` but the LOG file showed weird output with newlines. Let me fix the script and track file properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"1a25a71d15f8ed11b3446852b78a301088fb37375284dcf2fd4541eb1e84f1dd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d1265tqkmnt2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/emmy_last_email_id && echo \"---\" && /tmp/emmy_email_check_agent.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92,"output":117,"cacheRead":31040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31249,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777686204436,"responseId":"064489bc711e774c02f864a4cc46fb0a"}}
