{"type":"message","id":"e57be4e6","parentId":"36f4147f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:11:24.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"iCloud is working. I can see the emails via IMAP. The most recent email is from May 1, 2026. Now I need to:\n\n1. Save the password securely (using security keychain or a secure config file)\n2. Test the iCloud email check\n3. Make sure the cron job does both Gmail + iCloud\n\nLet me save the password and test a proper iCloud check. From the memory logs, I saw references to \"checkpoint\" with ID 14 for iCloud - meaning it was tracking the last seen email ID. But the FETCH command shows sequential numbers, not message IDs. Let me figure out a way to track what's been seen.\n\n\nI need to store the password in the Mac keychain so it can be accessed by the cron job, then build a script that queries both Gmail via gog and iCloud via IMAP, sends separate Telegram messages for each, and only reports truly new emails by tracking the last seen message ID for each account.\n","thinkingSignature":"aa8ce86e9a262c077162cea5e3fa223f544c6a2c7d50202c84e9ae2c24f59c37"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\niCloud connected ✅. Let me save the password and set up the full check.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c4us8egmfe9b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"security add-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -w \"xleb-qiqv-dged-sydy\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -U 2>&1 && echo \"SAVED\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1894,"output":294,"cacheRead":42464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44652,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777691479040,"responseId":"06449e57d83080b0d85a7ad696fdd560"}}
