{"type":"message","id":"209cba09","parentId":"63e4c371","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:04:15.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's saying the emails aren't being organized by urgency. Looking at the cron job, I do have the priority categories defined, but I need to make sure the agent actually implements them correctly. Let me check what happened with the last run and see if the priority labeling was actually applied.\n\nThe issue might be that the agent running the cron isn't actually reading the emails and categorizing them properly. The Gmail search returns results but the categorization step might not be working correctly.\n\nLet me think about what could be going wrong. When gog gmail search returns results, we then need to gog gmail get for each one to read the content and categorize. But maybe the agent isn't doing that step properly.\n\nActually, looking at the memory search results from earlier, I can see examples of what Bobby expects - the format shows:\n- 🔴 URGENT\n\n\n- 🟡 IMPORTANT  \n- ⚪ LOW PRIORITY\n\nThe last run seemed to have worked (the cron job ran successfully and delivered), but maybe Bobby didn't see the priority organization in the actual messages. I should check the recent cron run outputs to see if there are any errors or issues that might explain why the priority labeling isn't showing up.","thinkingSignature":"df3d1d805423863bf6e0dcc6a0c0e74514c95f8d63cfb271ae2a17bf497dfd77"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check what happened in the last run to see if the priority labeling went through:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jipeugnvk7ui_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"runs","jobId":"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":170,"output":316,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":59255,"totalTokens":59741,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","times