     \"sessionKey\": \"agent:emmy:cron:d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb:run:94ee89ac-62e3-4848-aa3e-4d06359fcb5a\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": 1776565766199,\n      \"jobId\": \"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb\",\n      \"action\": \"finished\",\n      \"status\": \"ok\",\n      \"summary\": \"✅ Email check done — no new emails.\",\n      \"runAtMs\": 1776565740525,\n      \"durationMs\": 25658,\n      \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776569340525,\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"usage\": {\n        \"input_tokens\": 1658,\n        \"output_tokens\": 396,\n        \"total_tokens\": 17406\n      },\n      \"delivered\": true,\n      \"deliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n      \"sessionId\": \"2a2bd7ed-feb5-4a1c-af79-63c35aad6b58\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:emmy:cron:d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb:run:2a2bd7ed-feb5-4a1c-af79-63c35aad6b58\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": 1776562155439,\n      \"jobId\": \"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb\",\n      \"action\": \"finished\",\n      \"status\": \"ok\",\n      \"summary\": \"✅ Email check done — no new emails.\",\n      \"runAtMs\": 1776562140506,\n      \"durationMs\": 14916,\n      \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776565740506,\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"usage\": {\n        \"input_tokens\": 17178,\n        \"output_tokens\": 232,\n        \"total_tokens\": 17342\n      },\n      \"delivered\": true,\n      \"deliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n      \"sessionId\": \"85455450-6050-485d-acd9-4645f12cc3ec\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:emmy:cron:d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb:run:85455450-6050-485d-acd9-4645f12cc3ec\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 773,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": 50,\n  \"hasMore\": true,\n  \"nextOffset\": 50\n}[... 39132 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["entries","total","offset","limit","hasMore","nextOffset"],"total":773},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777705455757}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7bb46b8","parentId":"666fb500","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:05:02.867Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the recent runs, I can see that when there ARE new emails, the priority labeling IS happening (🔴 URGENT, 🟡 IMPORTANT, ⚪ LOW PRIORITY). For example, looking at the run at ts=1777701839655:\n\n```\n📬 **Email Check — Complete**\n\n- **Gmail:** 3 new emails found\n- **iCloud:** No new emails (10 existing messages in INBOX, all from before this check window)\n```\n\nAnd earlier runs show properly labeled emails:\n- \"📬 **NEW MAIL (4 new)**\" with 🔴 URGENT, 🟡 IMPORTANT, ⚪ LOW PRIORITY\n\n\n- \"📬 **NEW MAIL (2 new)**\" with the same priority structure\n\nSo the labeling is working as intended. The confusion seems to be about what constitutes \"new\" emails. The current logic uses a timestamp file to track what's been seen, but if that timestamp doesn't exist or was recently updated, the agent may not be recognizing emails that have already been delivered to the inbox as \"new.\"\n\nLooking at the actual Gmail search results, I'm seeing emails from May 1st (19de5e6b3162ed52 at 19:12, 19de5c2ab79b2d55 at 13:15, 19de5963240d3029 at 18:08, and more) but the May 2nd emails aren't showing up in the results. This suggests the emails Bobby's concerned about might actually be from an earlier time period than the search is capturing.\n\nThe core issue seems to be that the Gmail results show 5 unread emails with various labels like Promotions, Updates, and Inbox, but when the agent ran the check, it only reported 3 new emails—which makes Bobby think some emails are being missed or reported as not new when they actually are.\n\nLooking at the search query more carefully, the timestamp-based approach should theoretically work since Gmail's `newer_than` maps to epoch time, but I'm not confident the agent is consistently converting and comparing timestamps that way. I need to review what actually happened in that specific run to see where the breakdown occurred.\n\nThe real problem might be that Bobby wants ALL unread emails in the inbox, not just ones from a time window—if emails sit unread for days, they'd never get flagged as \"new\" with this approach. Let me trace through what the agent actually did versus what Bobby is seeing now. The issue is that Gmail search with `newer_than:2h` might not properly filter by the timestamp comparison I intended. I'm looking at the categorization rules in the job definition, and I see they do include the priority labels Bobby wanted—Bills/Payments, Orders, Updates, and Other. Let me trace back through the most recent run to see why the labeling isn't appearing as expected.\n\nI found an earlier run with a detailed example that shows the format working correctly: the email from Capital One was properly flagged as URGENT with the Bills category, while ZipRecruiter was marked as IMPORTANT. So the priority labeling is actually functioning—the problem might be that today's emails weren't being categorized with those priority levels, which is what Bobby was frustrated about.\n\nLooking at the recent runs to understand the current state, I see there was an email from Y-12 Credit Union about an eStatement that arrived at 7:12pm, which should have been included in the 7:10pm search results. I'm trying to figure out if this email was properly categorized or if it slipped through without the priority labels applied. The email from Y-12 Credit Union about their eStatement should have been picked up in the search results I reviewed earlier, but the actual output doesn't show it listed. I'm realizing there's a discrepancy between what the agent is reporting as new emails and what actually came through in the search, which suggests the priority labeling or categorization might not be working as intended. The label format doesn't match what Bobby asked for—he specified his own priority categories like Bills/Payments, Orders, Updates, and Other, but the agent is applying the Gmail system labels instead. I need to correct this and use the proper categorization Bobby requested.\n\nLooking at the recent run summaries, I can see the issue now: one email was correctly labeled as 🔴 Bills/Payments but the other was mislabeled as 🔵 Updates when it should've been categorized differently. The agent is defaulting to the wrong label system instead of following Bobby's custom categories.\n\nThe core problem is that the agent isn't consistently reading email content to determine urgency—it's just guessing based on subject lines. I need to add clearer instructions requiring the agent to fetch each email's content and make a proper judgment about whether something is actually urgent (bills, payments, due dates) versus just an update or promotion. I need to make sure the agent is actually reading the email content before deciding on priority, since the subject line alone doesn't capture urgency. The timestamp filtering for Gmail might also be inconsistent, so I should clarify that the `newer_than:2h` window combined with comparing the email's date against the last checkpoint should catch truly new messages, though older unread emails could slip through if the window closes before the next check runs. The email was likely marked as UNREAD in Gmail but the search window of `newer_than:65m` didn't capture it if it arrived more than 65 minutes before the search ran. Since emails can arrive hours before the cron job checks them, I need to change the search strategy to either use a larger window like `newer_than:6h` or search all unread inbox emails and filter by a timestamp checkpoint instead.","thinkingSignature":"45fe683009aa66dfc9bd14a377c824fef98c9791fde1141157a859d277b75015"},{"type":"text","text":"I can see from past runs that the priority format was working before — emails got labeled as 🔴 URGENT, 🟡 IMPORTANT, etc. But looking at the most recent runs with actual emails, the agent isn't reading the email content to make better categorizations — it's mostly guessing from subject lines. Let me tighten up the instructions to make sure it always reads the email before labeling.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l046ytbu05yf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && date +%s"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51042,"output":1291,"cacheRead":27304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777705455759,"responseId":"0644d4f03f72824f4c65efdd8bf6fd0f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"055f930c","parentId":"c7bb46b8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:05:02.912Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l046ytbu05yf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1777705115\n---\n1777705502"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":38,"aggregated":"1777705115\n---\n1777705502","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777705502912}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d3131af","parentId":"055f930c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:05:19.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so the last check was at timestamp 1777705115. Let me check when that was:\n1777705115 seconds since epoch = May 2, 2026... let me calculate... that's about 389 seconds ago (about 6.5 minutes ago). That makes sense since the last run was at 1777705126304 (ms).\n\nNow let me check - the emails I found at 7:12pm were:\n- 19de5e6b3162ed52 at 2026-05-01 19:12\n\nThe last_email_check timestamp was 1777705115 which is May 2, 2026... let me convert:\n\n\nActually, 1777705115 - let me just check the date math quickly. 1777705115 / 86400 = about 20575 days since epoch... that's January 1970 which can't be right. Let me recalculate - Unix timestamps for 2026 should be around 1.77 billion, not 1.77 billion, so I'm off by a factor of 1000 somewhere. Actually no wait - 1777705115 is reasonable for 2026, let me verify: from 1970 to 2026 is roughly 56 years, which is about 56 * 365.25 * 86400 ≈ 1,766,000,000 seconds. So 1,777,705,115 would be somewhere in 2026, which checks out. If the last check was at 1777705115 and we're now at 1777705502, that's only about 387 seconds or 6-7 minutes ago, which aligns with the timing I was seeing. The emails from May 1 at 7:12pm ET wouldn't have been caught by the `newer_than:65m` filter since they arrived well over an hour before the search ran.","thinkingSignature":"98452b609d2e846343a5fcb9009a9bf9f54297e7cb403ee98b29b82802d8a921"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0qgcxwvajvg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"date -r 1777705115 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && date -r 1777705126 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52359,"output":447,"cacheRead":27304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80110,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777705502914,"responseId":"0644d51e957d6b01da7557bbf25eafe0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b4b974c","parentId":"0d3131af","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:05:19.628Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h0qgcxwvajvg_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sat May  2 02:58:35 EDT 2026\n---\nSat May  2 02:58:46 EDT 2026"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"Sat May  2 02:58:35 EDT 2026\n---\nSat May  2 02:58:46 EDT 2026","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777705519628}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b9e9089","parentId":"4b4b974c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:05:57.343Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, so the timestamp 1777705115 is May 2, 2026 at 2:58:35 AM EDT. The last check ran at 2:58 AM. The emails from May 1 at 7:12 PM (19:12) were received way before this - about 5.75 hours before. So the `newer_than:2h` search would find emails from the last 2 hours (so emails since 00:58 AM), and the Y-12 email from 7:12 PM the previous day wouldn't be in that window!\n\nThis is the bug. The timestamp comparison approach is designed to find \"new since last check\" but Gmail's `newer_than` only looks at emails received in the last X hours. \n\nThe real issue is that Bobby keeps seeing the same emails repeatedly because they're marked as unread in Gmail. My timestamp file approach was meant to filter these out, but I haven't been consistent with it. The system needs to track which emails have already been reported rather than just checking the received date. The timestamp approach has a fundamental flaw—I'm searching Gmail with a relative time window that keeps shifting, but then trying to compare against an absolute Unix timestamp stored from the last run, which creates a mismatch between what the search actually returns and what I'm checking against.\n\nThe real solution is to fetch all unread emails from the inbox without any time restriction, then compare each one against the stored timestamp to identify which ones are genuinely new since the last check.","thinkingSignature":"b755fa916868d8bc448dbadab018583edafeaf470b0fcfb201567d824c40d1d4"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue. The timestamp approach is broken — `newer_than:2h` only looks back 2 hours from \"now\", but I'm comparing against the stored LAST_CHECK timestamp which is an absolute Unix time. Gmail's `newer_than` doesn't work that way. The result: emails from 7pm are getting missed because they fall outside the moving 2-hour window.\n\nLet me fix this properly — fetch ALL unread emails, then filter by timestamp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_50f0i58v08b9_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb","patch":{"payload":{"message":"Check for new emails in Bobby's Gmail AND iCloud accounts. Send TWO separate Telegram messages — one for Gmail, one for iCloud.\n\n=== GMAIL CHECK ===\nSTEP 1: Read the last timestamp file:\nLAST_CHECK=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null)\nIf the file doesn't exist or is empty, set LAST_CHECK to 0.\n\nSTEP 2: Search Gmail for ALL unread inbox emails (no time limit — we filter by timestamp below):\ngog gmail search 'in:inbox is:unread' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\n\nSTEP 3: For each email found:\n- Read the email to get its full content: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n- Get the email's internalDate (Unix timestamp when Gmail received it)\n- ONLY process if internalDate > LAST_CHECK (email arrived AFTER the last check)\n- Skip emails where internalDate <= LAST_CHECK (already reported)\n\nSTEP 4: Also search Unroll.me/Unsubscribed:\ngog gmail search 'label:\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed\" newer_than:1d' --max 20 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\nFor any found, move to INBOX: gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove \"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed,CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS\" --add INBOX\n\nSTEP 5: Categorize each NEW email (only those with internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\n  🔴 Bills/Payments — financial obligations, bills, due dates, bank alerts, payments (Capital One, KUB, Flex, Affirm, Netflix, etc.)\n  🟡 Orders — shipping confirmations, receipts, order updates\n  🔵 Updates — service notifications, security alerts, account changes\n  ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promotions, marketing, social media\n\nSTEP 6: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for Gmail:\nIf NEW emails (internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\nIf NO new emails (all unread emails were <= LAST_CHECK): \"📬 GMAIL — No new emails\"\n\nSTEP 7: Update timestamp AFTER sending the report:\necho $(date +%s) > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp\n\n=== ICLOUD CHECK ===\nSTEP 8: Get iCloud credentials:\nICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)\n\nSTEP 9: Search iCloud INBOX for unseen emails:\ncurl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1\n\nSTEP 10: Get full envelope for new messages:\ncurl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1\n\nSTEP 11: Track with checkpoint file:\nLAST_ICLOUD=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n- Only process messages with msg_num > LAST_ICLOUD\n- After processing, update: echo <highest_msg_num> > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt\n\nSTEP 12: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for iCloud:\nIf new: \"📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\\n\\n[Sender — Subject]\"\nIf none: \"📬 ICLOUD — No new emails\"\n\nSTEP 13: If both have nothing new, send both \"no new emails\" messages."}}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52854,"output":1466,"cacheRead":27304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81624,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777705519630,"responseId":"0644d52f72175957c600d8c3e9afdd59"}}
{"type":"message","id":"93dbd568","parentId":"9b9e9089","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:06:03.454Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_50f0i58v08b9_1","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb\",\n  \"agentId\": \"emmy\",\n  \"name\": \"Emmy Email Check\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1773960428074,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"every\",\n    \"everyMs\": 3600000,\n    \"anchorMs\": 1773961081922\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"Check for new emails in Bobby's Gmail AND iCloud accounts. Send TWO separate Telegram messages — one for Gmail, one for iCloud.\\n\\n=== GMAIL CHECK ===\\nSTEP 1: Read the last timestamp file:\\nLAST_CHECK=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null)\\nIf the file doesn't exist or is empty, set LAST_CHECK to 0.\\n\\nSTEP 2: Search Gmail for ALL unread inbox emails (no time limit — we filter by timestamp below):\\ngog gmail search 'in:inbox is:unread' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 3: For each email found:\\n- Read the email to get its full content: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\\n- Get the email's internalDate (Unix timestamp when Gmail received it)\\n- ONLY process if internalDate > LAST_CHECK (email arrived AFTER the last check)\\n- Skip emails where internalDate <= LAST_CHECK (already reported)\\n\\nSTEP 4: Also search Unroll.me/Unsubscribed:\\ngog gmail search 'label:\\\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed\\\" newer_than:1d' --max 20 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\\nFor any found, move to INBOX: gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove \\\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed,CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS\\\" --add INBOX\\n\\nSTEP 5: Categorize each NEW email (only those with internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\\n  🔴 Bills/Payments — financial obligations, bills, due dates, bank alerts, payments (Capital One, KUB, Flex, Affirm, Netflix, etc.)\\n  🟡 Orders — shipping confirmations, receipts, order updates\\n  🔵 Updates — service notifications, security alerts, account changes\\n  ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promotions, marketing, social media\\n\\nSTEP 6: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for Gmail:\\nIf NEW emails (internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\\n\\n🔴 URGENT:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\\n\\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet]\\n\\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet]\\n\\nIf NO new emails (all unread emails were <= LAST_CHECK): \\\"📬 GMAIL — No new emails\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 7: Update timestamp AFTER sending the report:\\necho $(date +%s) > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp\\n\\n=== ICLOUD CHECK ===\\nSTEP 8: Get iCloud credentials:\\nICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\\\" -s \\\"emmy-icloud-email\\\" -w 2>/dev/null)\\n\\nSTEP 9: Search iCloud INBOX for unseen emails:\\ncurl -s --url \\\"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\\\" --user \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\\\" -X \\\"SEARCH UNSEEN\\\" 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 10: Get full envelope for new messages:\\ncurl -s --url \\\"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\\\" --user \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\\\" -X \\\"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\\\" 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 11: Track with checkpoint file:\\nLAST_ICLOUD=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"0\\\")\\n- Only process messages with msg_num > LAST_ICLOUD\\n- After processing, update: echo <highest_msg_num> > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt\\n\\nSTEP 12: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for iCloud:\\nIf new: \\\"📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\\\\n\\\\n[Sender — Subject]\\\"\\nIf none: \\\"📬 ICLOUD — No new emails\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 13: If both have nothing new, send both \\\"no new emails\\\" messages.\",\n    \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n    \"to\": \"8212808444\",\n    \"accountId\": \"emmy\",\n    \"bestEffort\": false\n  },\n  \"deleteAfterRun\": false,\n  \"state\": {\n    \"lastRunAtMs\": 1777705086566,\n    \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastDurationMs\": 39698,\n    \"lastDelivered\": true,\n    \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n    \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1777708686566,\n    \"consecutiveSkipped\": 0\n  },\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1777705561423\n}"}],"details":{"id":"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb","agentId":"emmy","name":"Emmy Email Check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1773960428074,"schedule":{"kind":"every","everyMs":3600000,"anchorMs":1773961081922},"sessionTarget":"isolated","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Check for new emails in Bobby's Gmail AND iCloud accounts. Send TWO separate Telegram messages — one for Gmail, one for iCloud.\n\n=== GMAIL CHECK ===\nSTEP 1: Read the last timestamp file:\nLAST_CHECK=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null)\nIf the file doesn't exist or is empty, set LAST_CHECK to 0.\n\nSTEP 2: Search Gmail for ALL unread inbox emails (no time limit — we filter by timestamp below):\ngog gmail search 'in:inbox is:unread' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\n\nSTEP 3: For each email found:\n- Read the email to get its full content: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n- Get the email's internalDate (Unix timestamp when Gmail received it)\n- ONLY process if internalDate > LAST_CHECK (email arrived AFTER the last check)\n- Skip emails where internalDate <= LAST_CHECK (already reported)\n\nSTEP 4: Also search Unroll.me/Unsubscribed:\ngog gmail search 'label:\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed\" newer_than:1d' --max 20 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\nFor any found, move to INBOX: gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove \"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed,CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS\" --add INBOX\n\nSTEP 5: Categorize each NEW email (only those with internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\n  🔴 Bills/Payments — financial obligations, bills, due dates, bank alerts, payments (Capital One, KUB, Flex, Affirm, Netflix, etc.)\n  🟡 Orders — shipping confirmations, receipts, order updates\n  🔵 Updates — service notifications, security alerts, account changes\n  ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promotions, marketing, social media\n\nSTEP 6: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for Gmail:\nIf NEW emails (internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\nIf NO new emails (all unread emails were <= LAST_CHECK): \"📬 GMAIL — No new emails\"\n\nSTEP 7: Update timestamp AFTER sending the report:\necho $(date +%s) > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp\n\n=== ICLOUD CHECK ===\nSTEP 8: Get iCloud credentials:\nICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)\n\nSTEP 9: Search iCloud INBOX for unseen emails:\ncurl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1\n\nSTEP 10: Get full envelope for new messages:\ncurl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1\n\nSTEP 11: Track with checkpoint file:\nLAST_ICLOUD=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n- Only process messages with msg_num > LAST_ICLOUD\n- After processing, update: echo <highest_msg_num> > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt\n\nSTEP 12: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for iCloud:\nIf new: \"📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\\n\\n[Sender — Subject]\"\nIf none: \"📬 ICLOUD — No new emails\"\n\nSTEP 13: If both have nothing new, send both \"no new emails\" messages.","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8212808444","accountId":"emmy","bestEffort":false},"deleteAfterRun":false,"state":{"lastRunAtMs":1777705086566,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":39698,"lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"nextRunAtMs":1777708686566,"consecutiveSkipped":0},"updatedAtMs":1777705561423},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777705563453}}
{"type":"message","id":"89969ff6","parentId":"93dbd568","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:06:11.785Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also reset the timestamp file to 0 so that on the next run, it picks up ALL current unread emails (since LAST_CHECK=0 means everything is \"new\"), so Bobby gets a fresh start with the proper priority-labeled emails.","thinkingSignature":"12c740fbd3451c5a81966eb093efee03b79279e0431750a5a1bff273bf056580"},{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. ✅ Now it fetches ALL unread emails from Gmail (no time window) then compares each against the timestamp. Only emails received after the last check get reported — and they get read first so the priority labels are accurate.\n\nWant me to reset the timestamp so the next run picks up all current unread emails fresh with proper labels?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55645,"output":123,"cacheRead":27304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777705563456,"responseId":"0644d55c2d8db6ff51d0906c05e6edbe"}}
